headline: Here's Why UPS Stock Failed to Deliver Last Year
summary: Shares of package delivery giant UPS (NYSE: UPS) fell by 19.8% in 2024, according to data provided by  S&P Global Market Intelligence.  It was a challenging year for the company operationally, and its adjusted operating profit is set to come in significantly lower for the year than originally expected.  The progression of the company's guidance throughout the year disappointed investors.
